[SN]TITLE[SN]
Radio election debate: Be in the audience for Highlands hustings

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Do you want to be in the audience of a special programme putting politicians under the spotlight?

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
BBC Scotland is hosting a series of TV and radio debates ahead of the Holyrood election on 5 May.
On 27 April, a hustings radio debate will be held in the Inverness and Nairn Constituency in The Maclean Room at Eden Court Theatre in Inverness.
Full details on the programme and how to apply to be in the audience can be found here.
The panel of politicians for the evening will comprise of the SNP's Fergus Ewing, Labour's David Stewart, the Liberal Democrat's Carolyn Caddic,  Edward Mountain for the Conservatives and John Finnie representing the Scottish Greens.
